---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import { SOCIAL_LINKS } from '../consts';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Who Rob Henry is and what this site is for."
	pubDate={new Date('May 11 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		I'm Rob Henry — a web developer who has spent years in the Microsoft ecosystem (.NET, ASP.NET
		MVC, Umbraco) and keeps stretching into whatever the rest of the stack is doing. This site is
		where I practice that in public: small experiments, notes, and the occasional post when
		something clicks.
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>What this site is.</strong> A personal home on the internet and a blog I update when I
		have something worth writing down — often about tools, workflows, or lessons from building
		things. It is not a portfolio agency site; it is a learning log that happens to be readable.
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>Why rebuild?</strong> The previous therobhenry.com ran on WordPress for years. I'm
		moving to Astro with content in Markdown, deploying through Cloudflare, and using Cursor to
		iterate. The goal is a fast, low-maintenance site I enjoy editing.
	</p>

	<p>
		If you find something useful here, I'd love to hear it. Comments may come later; for now, find
		me on{' '}
		{
			SOCIAL_LINKS.map((link, index) => (
				<>
					{index > 0 && (index === SOCIAL_LINKS.length - 1 ? ' or ' : ', ')}
					<a href={link.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						{link.name}
					</a>
				</>
			))
		}.
	</p>
</Layout>
